<br>
1) Jewelcraft has a low markup because it is far and away the easiest one to grandmaster.  To be a GM jeweler is nothing more than pp.  I could start a twink right now and be a GM jeweler in a couple hours.  Tailoring, Pottery, Smithing take loads more money and loads more time... Hence the markup.<br>
<br>
It's like going to going to school... You spend the time for that PHD you expect to paid better in the end.<br>
<br>
2) The Earing is never going to drop significantly in price.  I can still sell them easily for 15k and I highly doubt that will ever change until simply no one wants earings anymore.<br>
<br>
Reasons for this are simple.  The materials are a PAIN to get and you are not going to see people &quot;progressing&quot; to the level of tradeskills needed.  Robes are a pain.  Sickels are just HARD.  At 250 smithing I am lucky if I succeed on half the sickels I try.<br>
<br>
Point is the materials to make the earing have already dropped to a point where they aren't going to get any cheaper.  Thus the people who are making the earings are already selling at the minimum profit margin they are willing to except.<br>
