<br>
And to the person who said what if you use the opal stein for buying food and water... then don't buy one!  The vast majority of people who buy them, over time, will gain a lot of money.  But I always told bards not to buy them (they don't work with instruments and bards usually have enough charisma on other gear for their charming).  I mean, your arguement is like saying crystal spider fangs should be worth 50pp cause that's all they're good for if you're an enchanter and your melee skills stink.  Please.  But the vast majority of people will at some point hunt in Sebilis OR Seafuries in OOT OR do a tradeskill OR fight in a plain OR kill giants in Kunark... something involving large money transactions with vendors, and the steins pay off very fast.  So why begrudge the maker of the stien 200pp that they made, when you made back far more?  Which you will, unless you never level above 20, never sell or buy anything from a vendor, or some such.<br>
<br>
And to Chase... brewing ain't my buisiness, so I'm not saying this as someone you're competeing with... but please don't get frustrated and kill the market.  Really.  It only comes back to hurt you in the end.  Sometimes you have to lower your price, some times you have to talk to someone, sometimes the person won't listen and only wants to sell their stuff for any price, no matter what.  Best solution to the last situation is to lower your price right along with them when you know they're on... when they get below cost, buy their entire supply and go back to their old price.  Works like a charm.  Heh.  <br>
